<li>A relatively common congenital genetic condition which affects both males and females.</li>
<li>It used to be referred to as the male&nbsp;version of Turner syndrome.</li>
<li>However, the genetic causes of Noonan syndrome and Turner syndrome are distinct.</li>
<li>The principal&nbsp;features include congenital heart malformation, short stature, learning problems, indentation of the chest, impaired blood clotting,&nbsp;and a characteristic configuration of facial features.</li>
