<ul>
<li>The determination of oxygen-hemoglobin saturation of blood either by withdrawing a sample and passing it through a classical photoelectric oximeter or by electrodes attached to some translucent part of the body like finger, earlobe, or skin fold. It includes non-invasive oxygen monitoring by pulse oximetry.&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;code=C60832&amp;ns=NCI_Thesaurus">Source: NCI-THESAURUS</a></li>
