<ul>
<li>Pulmonary artery stenosis is a narrowing (stenosis) that occurs in the pulmonary artery, a large artery that sends oxygen-poor&nbsp;blood into the lungs to be enriched with oxygen.</li>
<li>Pulmonary artery stenting consists of moving a balloon dilation catheter into the&nbsp;narrowed area of the artery.</li>
<li>Stent placement is accomplished by positioning the balloon dilatation catheter and stent across the&nbsp;narrowed segment of the artery.</li>
<li>The balloon is inflated to its recommended pressure, expanding the stent and anchoring it in&nbsp;place.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul>
<li>Intention to perform the procedure is defined as having performed Proximal PA Stenting-specific pre-intervention measurements.</li>
</ul>', 'IMPACT Registry v1.0.1', NULL, 'Procedure - Proximal PA Stenting', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 719, '2016-09-14 15:57:00', '2018-10-11 08:20:16', NULL);
