	<li>2.A record of clinical study observations&nbsp;and other information that a study&nbsp;protocol designates must be completed&nbsp;for each subject.</li>
	<li>NOTE: In common&nbsp;usage, CRF can refer to either a CRF&nbsp;page, which denotes a group of one&nbsp;or more data items linked together for&nbsp;collection and display, or a casebook,&nbsp;which includes the entire group of CRF&nbsp;pages on which a set of clinical study&nbsp;observations and other information&nbsp;can be or have been collected, or&nbsp;the information actually collected by&nbsp;completion of such CRF pages for&nbsp;a subject in a clinical study [ICH E6&nbsp;Glossary]. See also CRF (paper).<br />
	&nbsp;</li>
