', NULL, '<p>Iung B, Cormier B, et al. Immediate results of percutaneous mitral commissurotomy. A predictive model on a series of 1514 patients. Circulation. 1996; 94: 2124-2130.</p>
', '<p><strong>Cormier score </strong>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Divided the patients into three groups depending on leaflets mobility and calcification and subvalvular affection:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Group 1, pliable noncalcified anterior mitral leaflet and mild subvalvular disease (i.e., thin chordae &gt;10 mm long);</li>
	<li>Group 2, pliable noncalcified anterior mitral leaflet and severe subvalvular disease (i.e., thickened chordae &lt;10 mm long); and</li>
	<li>Group 3, calcification of MV of any extent, as assessed by fluoroscopy, whatever the state of subvalvular apparatus &nbsp;</li>
</ul>

