', NULL, '<ul>
	<li>Atrioventricular nodal reciprocating tachycardia involves reciprocation between two functionally and anatomically distinct pathways. In most cases, the fast pathway&nbsp;appears to be located near the apex of Koch&nbsp;triangle.</li>
	<li>This triangle is bounded by the tendon of Tadaro superiorly, and the tricuspid annulus is the base.</li>
	<li>The slow pathway&nbsp;extends inferoposterior to the compact AV-node tissue and stretches along the septal margin of the tricuspid annulus at the level of, or slightly superior to, the coronarysinus, and constitutes generally the main target for ablation.</li>
	<li>Other pathways may be involved.</li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'CARDS EP ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 862, '2016-11-05 16:06:46', '2016-11-05 16:07:05', NULL);
