<p><strong>Step 2&nbsp;</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li>Measure loosely around the fullest part of your bust, with the tape straight across and around your back, bringing it to the front.</li>
	<li>Subtract your band measurement (from step 1) from this bust measurement.</li>
	<li>The difference calculates your bra size- each inch represents a cup size. For example, if you measure a 34 inch band size, and a 36 inch cup size, the difference is 2: which would indicate a B cup.&nbsp;<br />
